I think basic income is essentially about poverty and rethinking the way we treat poor people in our society.
I look at what is the highest feasible basic income we could have and then ask a separate question: Is pushing for this basic income worth the political effort?
Basic income is not only about trust, but also decency and not pushing individuals further into misery.
